Parses an ADQL query thanks to the Query() function.

This parser is able, thanks to a DBConsistency object, to check the consistency between the ADQL query to parse and the "database" on which the query must be executed. However the default DBConsistency object is an instance of DefaultDBConsistency which does no verification. Thus you must extend DBConsistency to ensure the consistency with the "database" on which the query must be executed.

To create an object representation of the given ADQL query, this parser uses a QueryBuilderTools object. So if you want customize some object (ie. CONTAINS) of this representation you just have to extend the corresponding default object (ie. ContainsFunction) and to extend the corresponding function of QueryBuilderTools (ie. createContains(...)).

WARNING: To modify this class it's strongly encouraged to modify the .jj file in the section between PARSER_BEGIN and PARSER_END and to re-compile it with JavaCC.
